  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Contract Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1. To manages and prepares all the cost estimates for tender projects.</p><p>2. Provide support in all upgrading projects and tender exercises.</p><p>3. Provide support in projects and ensure timely on claims submission to clients.</p><p>4. To ensure accurate and timely payment response on the monthly claim by subcontractors.</p><p>5. Provide contractual advisory to ensure the team to comply with contract obligations and procedures.</p><p>6. Provide advice and recommendation to meet clients’ business needs.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>1. Minimum 5 years ‘experience in Senior QS capacity.</p><p>2. Possess a Degree in Quantity Surveyor/Civil/Building/Construction Management.</p><p>3. Good working knowledge in contract law.</p><p>4. Possess following Soft Skills:</p><p>- Excellent communication and interpersonal skill</p><p>- Able to work under stress and prioritize tasks</p><p>- Resourceful</p><p>- Self-motivated with high degree of integrity</p><p>- Highly Organized</p><p>- Excellent time management skills</p>",
